{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "labs::make_loop::2.0", "icon": "make_loop_white", "tags": "sidefxlabs,  model, gamedev", "version": "2.0", "namespace": "labs"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Labs Make Loop"], "extent": [0, 19]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": [" Takes a mesh or volume that is animated and loops them "], "extent": [137, 201]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This node will make either a mesh, volume or particle effect loop. "], "extent": [201, 270]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The general idea is that it will offset the animation by half of the timeline and then do a sinewave to blend between the two animations. "], "extent": [270, 410]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This will work with meshes with constant topology or volumes, or with particles coming out of a popnet with the right attributes."], "extent": [410, 541]}, {"type": "col_group", "body": [{"ext": null, "type": "col", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [541, 547], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/make_loop_before.gif", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/images/make_loop_before.gif"}], "extent": [547, 593]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Mesh sequence before looping applied "], "extent": [593, 636]}], "container": true}, {"ext": null, "type": "col", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [636, 642], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/make_loop_after.gif", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/images/make_loop_after.gif"}], "extent": [642, 683]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Mesh sequence after looping applied "], "extent": [683, 725]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [725, 731], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If you set the time range too short for particles, all particles will be removed before looping; You will therefore have to modify their lifespan settings accordingly. You need the following attributes from a particle system to get it to work: @life, @age."], "extent": [731, 994]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [994, 1006], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Start Frame"], "extent": [1006, 1023], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Beginning of the Loop"], "extent": [1023, 1053]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["End Frame"], "extent": [1053, 1068], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["End of the loop"], "extent": [1068, 1092]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Number of Loops"], "extent": [1092, 1113], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Times to repeat the loop"], "extent": [1113, 1147]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "text": "Parameters"}], "title": ["Labs Make Loop"], "summary": [" Takes a mesh or volume that is animated and loops them "]}